About Dallas County

Other gems in the feather in the State of Texas are the cities of Dallas, Fort Worth, and San Antonio, which offer a huge range of attractions to their visitors. The city of Dallas, which is the county seat of Dallas County, along with Fort Worth is one of the metropolitan areas of the US. The city holds historical importance for being a prominent center of the oil and cotton industries. If you are one of those seeking adventures in this land, then definitely Dallas County is your place, the ruins of the Old Cahawba cannot be missed here. It is an archeological park that possesses many natural wonders. Old Depot Museum, Sturdivant Hall, and the Vaughan-Smitherman Museum are other important places of archeological importance in the county.
